node.text:
I was feeling quite heartbroken and heavy the week I chatted with Russell, but he was absolutely kind, inquisitive and insightful as can be. I am very grateful for the opportunity to chat and to share parts of my story. Hope we can get the dogs together next. 

Link in bio to view a segment on YouTube! Or catch the whole 1 hour 38 minute conversation via @russellbrand’s podcast Under a the Skin on @hearluminary.

node.title: Spirituality In The Modern World with @russellbrand

node.text:
Join @oreggieglobal, me, Benji, and the energy of people across the globe as we connect on the power of TRANSITION. Take some some for the breath, and lovingly ask yourself... what wisdom of the winter will you take with you into Spring? Remember... how you move matters. 

Thank you so much to Reggie for sharing his heart and teachings so freely. Becoming friends with you is definitely a gift I am grateful and honored to take with me into Spring. 
ALSO, FELIZ CUMPLEAÑOS @activepeaceyoga! Join Reggie for practice this weekend! See his latest post for the schedule Saturday and Sunday. 
Monday, your new Yoga For Renewal practice hits YWA YouTube channel - expect a lot of good hip work. 

We got you covered baby. 
CUE: What’s Going On 🎶 

Happy FWFG FRIDAY 🐣💜
#activepeaceyoga #findwhatfeelsgood

node.title: RENEWAL live chat with Reggie Hubbard!

A & A coming together from London to Austin to chat, connect, and breathe together. 

Join us for conversation followed by a beautiful breath practice, which will leave you feeling more more _______. Fill in the blank and share with us below. 

Follow @aichamckenzie and @breathebyamck for more. Pair daily breathe session with AMCK with your daily yoga practice with YWA this coming week for a proper reset. 

This session was recorded live with community tuning in from ALL around the globe. If you attended the live - we would love to celebrate your presence there by hearing from you down below! 💫

Aicha, thank you. Let’s do it again soon, and Happy Mother’s Day to you and all the mums. 💛

#breathebyamck #yogawithadriene

*note* a new wave of AMCK Breathe spray coming soon, we will keep you posted!

node.text:
As a cattle dog, Benji is just the best at communicating and herding! He really loves to take naps... but he also really loves to help! He quite enjoys a good task to focus on when it’s time to get to work. He likes to bring people together (he is dictating this to me now) he likes to see people be good to each other, and he loves toys and playing - especially tennis. Favorite food: chips. Favorite person: you. (oh he is talking to me!)

💙💜🧡💖💛💚🤎
I could not be more proud of him and am excited to share VOTE WITH BENJI, with all of you! 

With art and animation by the amazing  @wilbo_rose , original music by the one and only @spacejason3d , and story by @the_realjeffmills and myself, inspiration by Benji and our beloved community. Sending a special thank you and high five to @the_realjeffmills for producing and directing this baby. While we missed going on tour this year, we are certainly grateful to know we can always create, engage, and share in both fun and meaningful conversation with all of you. For me, it has always been a huge part of what taking our yoga off the mat looks like. (Though we do miss those 3 hour hug lines!) 

Please join us, join Benji, and let’s get out the vote. 🗳

Benji has launched a friendly and easy to use website that can assist you with all your voting needs like checking registration, finding your poll location, or reading up on Covid 19 voting info.

Visit www.votewithbenji.com and share with your friends!
#votewithbenji #votéconbenji #vote

With hearts and ears wide open,⁣
dive in with me for this incredibly⁣
engaging and informative IG LIVE.⁣
⁣
I delved into a chat about my yoga journey, on and off the mat, we experienced a beautiful collective healing Sound Bath Meditation by @phyllicia.bonanno, followed by a wonderfully enlightening conversation with @iamrachelricketts centering anti-racism and spiritual activism. ⁣
⁣
So so good! 🥰  Thank you to everyone who joined in! Please share your thoughts with me below! 🙏🏾👇🏾

node.text:
⁣
⁣
I’m super excited to be taking over Adriene’s instagram today to connect with you all in such a transformative way.⁣
⁣
I’m Tie Simpson, a mother of two, Yoga Instructor, Artist, Wellness Influencer, Content Creator, and the Founder of @sistersofyoga who’s hosting the #ShareTheMicNow Yoga Edition this weekend. I’ve been practicing yoga and on my spiritual journey for about 7 years now, and I’m so incredibly grateful to spend the day with you. ⁣
⁣
Stay tuned today in the FEED + STORIES, where I’ll be sharing my yoga philosophy, my practice, “A Day In The Life” with me, resources on how you can help to expand the collective forward, and connecting through Q&A.
⁣
THANK YOU ADRIENE for your love, light, and your unwavering support of this initiative to amplifying black and brown voices in the yoga and wellness community.⁣
⁣
I’ll be going LIVE today at 12:20PM EST to connect with you all! ⁣
12:30PM- @phyllicia.bonanno will lead us in a collective healing soundbath meditation⁣
1PM EST- @iamrachelricketts will share her wisdom and heart work centered around dismantling racism through spiritual activism. ⁣
⁣
Let’s connect below. 🥰👇🏾 Say Hiiii, and tell me one thing you’re grateful for today!

node.text:
After almost 14 months of solid VIRTUAL live events, I took June off from virtual to reset - and thank goodness I did because I was able to swiftly show up for Mama Rose when she needed me most. But I AM BACK - TONIGHT! TONIGHT! Cue West Side Story, or Smashing Pumpkins, whichever you want. 

I am so very honored and happy to join my friend @mynameisjessamyn in conversation and celebration of her most recent book YOKE. 

This first slide is us with badasses @allymisslove and @nikkihiltz in JANUARY 2020, look at our innocence. Mid 2020 in the thick of lockdown, I had the total privilege of reading YOKE before publishing. I was giddy! I have memories of sitting on my tiny concrete back stoop, amongst my attempt at a victory garden, laughing, crying, shaking my head in all the ways, and ultimately beaming with a deep sense of respect, fellowship, and gratitude for Jessamyn. Full stop. To get a sense of how and why I am fully showing up for this book, and why it’s so important you just have to read it, take in her words, certainly not mine. 
Hope we can meet and cheese in person again soon, until then, how about tonight on Zoom - ever heard of it? 5pm MT, 6pm CT, 7pm ET. $5. Link in bio to register. 💛 swipe to see the book and get your copy pronto. #yokebook

node.text:
July is here. Join me for a month long of practices curated to guide you, hold you, lift you, and support you through your current PROCESS. This collection, calendar and playlist is free, so we can all practice together. 

This month’s curation of practices are about healing, but they are also about trying new things, seeing things from another angle, building new muscle, and ultimately forgiveness.

“We cannot have a healed society, we cannot have change, we cannot have justice, if we do not reclaim and repair the human spirit.” 
- @zenchangeangel 

♥

Link in bio to hop in today JULY 1. 
Or tomorrow JULY 2.
Brand NEW upload JULY 5. 

#ywaprocess

node.text:
Meditation for Mom. 🌹
Fresh love letter in your box tomorrow. A bit of my heart on the page after a week of being with Mom in hospital. I decided after almost ten years of writing some of you, I had to write, as family. I had to let you in on my week, as I have done for almost a decade. 
But don’t worry, I always come bearing gifts, offerings for you, your health, and for your families. 
Your well being is my well being. 
This is our exchange. This is the practice. So open your love letter to find your free practice for the day tomorrow, along with your July free calendar, our community contemplation, and more. I’m always in your corner. Thank you for being in mine. 
All the love… and roses. 🥰
A
